race.comment: The scratching of the stablemate looks a positive for FIFI BLUE (2) who must be going as good as her well-fancied stablemate. She didn't fire a shot last start but was good when resuming at Swan Hill over the mile. Strips fitter and will appreciate the rise in trip. Bold showing anticipated. DIVINE CONCLUSION (1) showed good early muster and fought on to finish third last start over 1800m at Wagga Riverside. No tougher this time but carries the big weight again. Will take another strong account of himself. NAJLE (4) last raced when successful by a neck over 2069m at Moe three-and-a-half months ago. Is treated to the services of McDougall fresh and has been readied with two jump-outs. Can feature in the finish. PEARL TROUT (5) has been solid in his last three without saluting. Yet to be tested over this journey but is worth safe keeping.
